Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Velociraptor: Capture a memory dump

Capture a memory dump for an infected process

Dumping a memory process is a must during the DFIR process, and bear in mind that we will cover this in detail later in the course. It will get interesting. 

As demonstrated, we now know how to search for an artifact by clicking on Client ID C.2b3a22f66b1c0ad6.

Velociraptor made it a piece of cake when dumping memory for a specific process. All you need to do is:

  1. Identify the process name you want to dump using Windows.System.Pslist artifact.
  2. Use Windows.Triage.ProcessMemory artifact to dump the memory.
  3. Download the dump into your investigation machine.

 

Get the process name you want to dump its memory.

 

Use the process name you captured from PsList. Note that it placed the process name without .exe.
